@startuml
title SomeTrails Subscription Management
actor User
participant "SomeTrails"          as ST
participant "Settings"            as SET
participant "Subscription Page"   as SP
participant "Tier Selector"       as TS
participant "Payment Form"        as PF
participant "Payment Processor"   as PAY
participant "Subscription Service"    as SUB
participant "User Database"       as DB
participant "Email Service"       as ES

== Access Subscription ==
User -> ST   : Navigate to Settings
ST   -> SET  : Open settings menu
User -> SET  : Select "Manage Subscription"
SET  -> SP   : Open subscription page
SP   -> SUB  : Fetch current tier
SUB  -> DB   : Query user subscription
DB   --> SUB : Return tier info
SUB  --> SP  : Display current tier + options

== Upgrade Subscription ==
User -> SP   : Select "Upgrade"
SP   -> TS   : Show available upgrade tiers
TS   --> User: Present Plus / Peak options
User -> TS   : Select target tier
TS   -> PF   : Request payment info

alt Credit Card
    User -> PF   : Enter card details
    PF   -> PAY  : Submit card for processing
else PayPal / Stripe
    User -> PF   : Select processor
    PF   -> PAY  : Redirect to processor
    PAY  --> User: Authenticate on processor
    User -> PAY  : Authorize payment
end

PAY  --> SUB : Payment confirmed
SUB  -> DB   : Update subscription tier
DB   --> SUB : Updated
SUB  -> ES   : Send receipt email
ES   --> User: Deliver receipt
SUB  --> ST  : Refresh with new tier access

== Cancel Subscription ==
User -> SP   : Select "Cancel"
SP   -> SUB  : Check current tier
SUB  --> SP  : Return tier

alt Base User
    SP   --> User: Nothing to cancel
else Plus or Peak User
    SP   --> User: Show confirmation prompt
    User -> SP   : Confirm cancellation
    SP   --> User: Request cancellation reason
    User -> SP   : Submit reason
    SP   -> SUB  : Process cancellation
    SUB  -> PAY  : Cancel recurring billing
    PAY  --> SUB : Cancellation confirmed
    SUB  -> DB   : Update subscription status
    DB   --> SUB : Updated
    SUB  -> ES   : Send cancellation email
    ES   --> User: Deliver confirmation
    SUB  --> SP  : Confirm cancellation
end

== Exit ==
User -> SP   : Select "Exit"
SP   --> ST  : Return to logged-in site

@enduml
